\chapter{ES6 Promises}

The first example is from [sons of javascript](https://medium.com/sons-of-javascript/javascript-an-introduction-to-es6-1819d0d89a0f#.g80rh59zx) and illustrates the basic use of promises in ES6. In ES6 a Promise is an Object, which is normally returned from an asynchronous operation.

\begin{codeblock}
'use strict'
var longFn = function() {
  return new Promise(function(res, rej) {
    setTimeout(res, 1000);
  });
};

var coolFn = function() {
  log('cool');
};

// logs cool after 1 second
longFn().then(coolFn);
\end{codeblock}